{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"nonglacial-tense-vulture","description":"# BUG: outbound field-allowlist drops are silent\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Have a local field that maps to Jira but is not in the outbound update allowlist.\n2. Change it locally; run reconcile.\n\n**Expected:** a deduped alert notes the dropped field (mirroring the unmapped-status alert).\n**Actual:** the field is dropped silently at `apply_outbound.py:117-124` with no signal — the only\nplace the reconciler degrades without telling anyone.\n\n## What / files\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_outbound.py:117-124` — emit a deduped BRIDGE_ALERT on drop.\n- Mirror the pattern at `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/fetcher.py:180-234` (unmapped-status alert).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] An outbound field dropped by the update allowlist emits a deduped alert.\n- [ ] Alert is deduped per (ticket, field) so it does not spam every pass.\n- [ ] Regression test asserting the alert fires on a dropped field.\n","id":"acd0-852a-a5e5-4738","parent_id":"ace2-f784-4b19-4f22","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Silent outbound field-allowlist drop: no observability"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783470419404410001,"uuid":"b669239b-4b96-48fa-ae22-8688e0213d48"}